title: Diffusion Indexes of Industrial Production: Diffusion Index of Industrial Production, One Month Earlier
notes:
Diffusion Index of Industrial Production (DIFF) are diffusion indexes of industrial production calculated as the percentage of series that increased over the indicated span (one, three, or six months) plus one-half the percentage that were unchanged.

For more information, see the explanatory notes (https://www.federalreserve.gov/releases/g17/About.htm) issued by the Board of Governors. For recent updates, see the announcements (https://www.federalreserve.gov/feeds/g17.html) issued by the Board of Governors

Source Code: DIFF.DIFFUSION_1.S
